import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.hist(data['delay'], bins=30, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Delay Time')
    plt.axvline(data['delay'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['delay'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Delay Time')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of delay time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    # Calculate the average distance
    avg_distance = data['distance'].mean()

    # Create a bar chart of distance
    plt.bar(['Average Distance'], [avg_distance], color='blue')

    # Add a horizontal line for the average distance
    plt.axhline(avg_distance, color='red', linestyle='--', label=f'Average Distance: {avg_distance:.2f}')

    # Set the chart title
    plt.title('What is the average distance traveled by flights?', wrap=True)

    # Add a legend
    plt.legend()

    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['origin_destination'] = data['origin'] + '-' + data['destination']
    origin_destination_counts = data['origin_destination'].value_counts().reset_index()
    origin_destination_counts.columns = ['origin_destination', 'count']
    origin_destination_counts['origin'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[0])
    origin_destination_counts['destination'] = origin_destination_counts['origin_destination'].apply(lambda x: x.split('-')[1])

    pivot_table = origin_destination_counts.pivot('origin', 'destination', 'count')
    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 8))
    sns.heatmap(pivot_table, cmap='coolwarm', annot=True, fmt='.0f')
    plt.title('Which origin and destination pairs are the most common?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Destination')
    plt.ylabel('Origin')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.yticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    data.boxplot(column='delay', by='origin', ax=ax)
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of delay time by origin?')
    ax.set_xlabel('Origin')
    ax.set_ylabel('Delay Time')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.suptitle('')
    plt.legend(title='Origin', loc='upper right')
    
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
